# <type>(<scope>): <subject>        ← 70 chars max; imperative mood
#
# type  : feat | fix | refactor | test | docs | chore | ci | perf | revert
# scope : optional; e.g. config, tools, deploy, shell, git, ssh, secrets
# !     : append before the colon to flag a breaking change
#
# Body (required) — blank line after subject, wrap at 72 chars.
# Summarise what changed and explain WHY this approach was chosen.
# Call out any decisions, trade-offs, or alternatives that came up
# during implementation — especially if there were open questions or
# back-and-forth before settling on this solution.


# Footer (optional)
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
# Closes #<issue>
